---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Terms — ByteWorks';
const description =
  'Service Levels & Updates Policy, support hours, backups and ownership terms for ByteWorks clients.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description} image="/og-image.svg" lang="en">
  <section class="px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16 max-w-4xl mx-auto py-14 md:py-20">
    <header class="mb-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold">Terms</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
        Service Levels & Updates Policy for ByteWorks websites.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Service Levels & Updates Policy -->
    <section class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Service Levels &amp; Updates Policy</h2>

      <h3>1. Maintenance &amp; Monitoring</h3>
      <p>
        All active plans include hosting, domain, SSL certificates, and automatic weekly backups.
        ByteWorks monitors uptime and site integrity periodically, performing preventive maintenance
        every quarter or when critical updates are required.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Support Hours &amp; Response Time</h3>
      <p>
        Support is provided Monday to Friday, from 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM (AST).
        Communication channels include WhatsApp and email. Response times are based on the request type:
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="table-auto w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <th class="text-left py-2">Type</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2">Example</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2">Target Response Time</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">Critical issue</td>
              <td class="py-2">Site offline, SSL expired, broken form</td>
              <td class="py-2">≤ 4 business hours</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">Standard support</td>
              <td class="py-2">Update request, content change</td>
              <td class="py-2">≤ 24 business hours</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">General inquiries</td>
              <td class="py-2">Billing, feature questions</td>
              <td class="py-2">≤ 48 business hours</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        Requests received outside business hours are processed the next business day.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Monthly Updates Scope</h3>
      <p>
        Each plan includes a defined number of updates per month, measured in task units or time blocks.
        Tasks do not roll over from month to month.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="table-auto w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <th class="text-left py-2">Plan</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2">Monthly Updates</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2">Approx. Time per Task</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">Start</td>
              <td class="py-2">1</td>
              <td class="py-2">up to 30 min</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">Pro</td>
              <td class="py-2">2</td>
              <td class="py-2">up to 45 min each</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">Elite</td>
              <td class="py-2">3</td>
              <td class="py-2">up to 60 min each</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 font-medium">E-Commerce Pro</td>
              <td class="py-2">4</td>
              <td class="py-2">up to 60 min each</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-3"><strong>Examples of included updates:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Text or image replacement</li>
        <li>Color or layout adjustment</li>
        <li>Product or service information edit</li>
        <li>Adding a new testimonial or section within scope</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3"><strong>Not included:</strong> new pages, redesigns, additional stores, or complex integrations (these require a quote or plan upgrade).</p>

      <h3>4. E-Commerce Product Limit</h3>
      <p>
        The E-Commerce Pro plan includes up to 20 active products.
        If the catalog exceeds this limit, the <em>Extended Catalog</em> Add-on applies (+$25/month per block of 20 products).
        Catalogs exceeding 60 products require a custom <em>E-Commerce Plus</em> plan.
        These limits ensure performance, predictable maintenance time, and proper optimization.
      </p>

      <h3>5. Backups &amp; Security</h3>
      <p>
        Backups are performed automatically once every 7 days and stored securely.
        Restores caused by client-side deletion or external changes are available on request.
        Security monitoring covers SSL validity, file integrity, and critical dependency updates.
      </p>

      <h3>6. Ownership &amp; Access</h3>
      <p>
        ByteWorks retains technical ownership of the hosting and maintenance environment during the active subscription period.
        Clients retain full ownership of their brand assets, domain, and site content.
        Upon cancellation, ByteWorks can provide a downloadable version of the site and data upon request.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</Base>
